BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 12 KYODO -- The Export-Import Bank of 
Japan said Tuesday [12 April] it has signed a protocol for an 
untied direct loan of up to 200 million U.S. dollars to 
Nacional Financiera S.N.C. (Nafin) of Mexico. 
  The funds will be used for financing such projects as 
installing emissions control facilities to reduce air pollution 
in the Mexico City area, the Japanese bank said. 
  The funds are being extended in line with Japan's "Funds for 
Development" initiative program launched last June, the bank 
said. 

